Before using shared MCP guidance or connecting external tools, read and follow:

1. `~/.ai-registry/capability-routing.md`
2. `~/.ai-registry/mcp/mcp.md`

Use this template when the target project should dynamically route to MCP servers without adopting shared workflow orchestration or skill routing.

If the agent is dispatched as a subagent, it must not select its own workflow or role. It must follow the role, task, expected outputs, acceptance criteria, and handoff instructions assigned by the primary agent. A subagent may route to MCP only within its assigned role and task scope.

Ask before OAuth, API keys, tokens, account access, private workspace access, private data access, or remote mutations.

Local repository instructions override shared registry guidance when more specific.
If `~/.ai-registry` is unavailable, state that and continue with local instructions only.
